l. 16. dominia. The definition here given of demesne differs from that in use in later times. It means all the land which has not been granted out in see, and thus includes all land held by servile tenants. At a later date land held by a manin dominio is the land actually in his own hands, land held in servicio is the land held of him by whatever tenure.
